New Records: Travis Head scored a career-best hundred
Mitchell Marsh took nine wickets from his spinners
Key Match Events: Travis Head's unbeaten 154 sealed Australia's 13th straight ODI win
Ben Duckett and Will Jacks built a platform for England before the middle order collapse
Marnus Labuschagne took a career-best three for 39 from six overs
Pre-Game Insights: Australia were supposedly depleted due to injuries and the virus that swept through their camp
England's interim white-ball head coach, Marcus Trescothick, expected a tough match
Post-Match Reflections: Harry Brook, the stand-in England captain, acknowledged that England did some good things but couldn't sustain it for longer periods
Marcus Trescothick praised Travis Head as a serious player
Miscellaneous Highlights: The pitch got better as the game progressed, affecting the outcome
Ben Dwarshuis made his ODI debut and took four overs
Travis Head's innings was a masterclass, reminiscent of his performance in the World Cup win in Ahmedabad last November
